stimulus:
Instructions

You will see images of two categories of alien fruits, named sprock and blicket .

They will come out in random order, one at a time.

For one category, press the "F" key, and for the other category, press the "J" key.

You won't know which key corresponds to which fruit at first, but make your best guesses and over time, you will learn.

Remember, you will use the "F" and "J" keys to categorize the fruits.

Press the space bar to begin.

stimulus:
Thank you for completing this experiment!

This experiment is a replication of previous work on category learning from direct experience showing that people categorize typical members of a category more quickly than atypical ones. In this case, we are looking to see if participants are faster to categorize alien fruits that are more typical of their categories (closer to the center of the size distribution of the category). That is, participants will categorize big sprocks and small blickets more quickly than small sprocks and big blickets.

Thank you for your participation!

stimulus:
Thank you for completing this experiment!

This experiment is a replication of previous work on category learning from direct experience showing that people categorize typical members of a category more quickly than atypical ones. In this case, we are looking to see if participants are faster to categorize alien fruits that are more typical of their categories (closer to the center of the size distribution of the category). That is, participants will categorize big tomas and small botis more quickly than small tomas and big botis.

Thank you for your participation!
